definitions.definition: No longer in use; gone into disuse ; disused or neglected (often in favour of something newer).
examples: Speedy, worldwide, accessible delivery of news through the Web has made newspapers obsolete .
Horses became obsolete means of transportation in cities in the first half of the twentieth century.

main_definition: ( of words, equipment, etc. ) No longer in use; gone into disuse ; disused or neglected (often in favour of something newer).
secondary_definitions: ( biology ) Imperfectly developed; not very distinct.
